<subSubSection id="36F5FD9F855CFF8BEBA0FE32FCD5FDE5" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="7E50AE14855CFF8BEBA0FE32FCD5FDE5" blockId="2.[151,1437,333,576]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">
<emphasis id="4C9B7206855CFF8BEBA0FE32FE88FE22" bold="true" box="[199,314,477,504]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Dark-bluish metallic species. Lunule orange; without frontal protuberance; frons somewhat swollen. Arista and eye bare. Hyaline wing except for the brown-pigmented pterostigma; wing entirely microtrichose. Crossvein r-m located slightly beyond the end of subcostal vein.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
